Gauteng's education department has welcomed the arrest of a 20-year old grade 11 pupil. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng's Education Department has welcomed the arrest of a 20-year old grade 11 pupil. It's alleged he stabbed to death a fellow pupil outside Forest High School in Johannesburg. Another 18-year-old and a 15-year-old were also wounded. The dead pupil's mother couldn't contain her grief as she went to identify the lifeless body. READ: Update: Learner stabbed to death, murder case opened For the Gauteng Education Department, this has become a common sight. MEC Panyaza Lesufi said he is aware of challenges at this particular school. Mid-year exams at the school have been suspended for now. eNCA reporter Lindokuhle Xulu has more details on the story in the video above.